summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2009 DODGE JOURNEY. WHILE DRIVING 35 MPH, THE VEHICLE WAS CRASHED. THE DETAILS OF THE CRASH WERE UNAVAILABLE. THE AIR BAGS DID NOT DEPLOY. THERE WERE INJURIES TO THE CONTACT'S KNEES AND LOWER BACK THAT REQUIRED MEDICAL ATTENTION. A POLICE REPORT WAS FILED. THE VEHICLE WAS REPAIRED, BUT THE DETAILS WERE NOT AVAILABLE. THE MANUFACTURER WAS MADE AWARE OF THE FAILURE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 51,000.
